CITY LAYER
Apex Chronicles | Canonical City Mechanics Specification
STATUS: Draft

---

1. FOUNDATIONAL PHILOSOPHY — MIRRORS NOT GATES

City buildings reflect and deepen what the player has done in runs. They do
not control what the player can access. This principle applies universally
across all city buildings with no exceptions.

The relationship between runs and city is inseparable but asymmetric:
- Runs write the story
- The city remembers it

Discovery is always free. The full hero power pool is available from run one
regardless of city state. What the city provides is the infrastructure for
mastery — not the conditions for access.

No city building gates a power from appearing in a run. No construction
project unlocks a combo. Combos are discovered in runs and recorded in the
lair. The city deepens what the player has earned. It does not withhold what
the player hasn't yet unlocked.

---

2. THE CITY AS A PLACE

The city is pre-existing and struggling when the player arrives. It is not
built from scratch — it is restored. The hero does not construct a city.
They wake one up.

The run layer and city layer share the same underlying street map. The player
is always in their city. The Core Four buildings — Science Lab, Training
Center, Tailor Shop, and Hero's Lair — are consistent landmarks recognizable
in both layers across all four stages.

Cosmetic city improvements within a stage do not propagate granularly into
the run layer. The run layer reflects stage-level visual identity only — not
every incremental aesthetic change.

Stage One is a city on its last legs. Boarded windows. Cracked streets.
Enough intact buildings to believe there is still life and population. Few
enough to believe the city is struggling. Not dead — but close.

---

3. THE TUTORIAL ARC — STAGE ONE BUILDINGS

The tutorial arc consists of four restorable buildings unlocked through
specific run type completion. World-based nudges — broadcasts, visible crises
— guide players toward specific locations during the tutorial. When they
arrive, the situation presents itself as a run type naturally. Only one
mission type is available per tutorial run. After tutorial completion, all
three are available simultaneously.

Tutorial sequence:

SCIENCE LAB
Unlocked by: completing an Intel / Horde Survival run
Teaches: support skills
Narrative: The lab was in crisis. A broadcast sends the hero there. The
situation demands intel work. The scientist's name is cleared as a result
of what the hero discovered.
City role: Reflects and deepens support skill use discovered in runs.

TRAINING CENTER (Stage One form: The Gym)
Unlocked by: completing a Boss Fight run
Teaches: hero powers
Narrative: The gym owner needed help with the gang boss controlling the
neighborhood. The hero dealt with it.
City role: Houses the hero power deepening system. In Stage One it is a
basic gym — functional, humble, recently rescued. The hero power deepening
system is NOT active during the tutorial stage. It activates at Stage Two.

TAILOR SHOP
Unlocked by: completing an Escort Defense run
Teaches: cosmetics and appearance customization
Narrative: The tailor was being terrorized. The hero protected them.
City role: Houses cosmetic customization and identity expression.

AREA BOSS DEFEATED — Tutorial arc milestone
Completes the tutorial arc. Player has demonstrated mastery across all
three run types. Triggers the Hero's Lair unlock.

HERO'S LAIR
Unlocked by: area boss defeat — earned, not found.
Not a restoration. The city gives the hero a headquarters because they
proved they were staying.
Houses: combo discovery log, achievement displays, unlocked name history,
cosmetic loadout management, run statistics.
The most dramatic mirror in the city — because combo discovery is the most
dramatic moment in a run.

