4. CITY STAGES — FOUR VISUAL AND MECHANICAL STATES

The city develops through four visual stages tied to player progression and
playtime. Each stage is mechanically a distinct run environment — same streets,
higher stakes. Stage progression is driven by overall run completion and
progression, not by specific building restoration.

STAGE ONE — RUNDOWN
Visual identity: Boarded windows. Cracked streets. Barely alive. Enough
intact buildings to believe there is still life and population, few enough
to believe the city is on its last legs.
Run environment: Tutorial. Constrained geography, limited complexity. One
mission type per run, heavily nudged by world broadcasts.
Difficulty: Lowest.
Training Center form: The Gym. Basic. Humble. Functional. Recently rescued.

STAGE TWO — DEVELOPING
Visual identity: City visibly recovering. Construction visible. Signs of
life returning to neighborhoods.
Run environment: All three mission types available simultaneously. Increasing
enemy density and challenge.
Difficulty: Mid-game.
Training Center form: The Complex. The gym gets built out. Hero power
deepening system comes online for the first time. Sections activate as
powers are proven in runs.

STAGE THREE — REFINED
Visual identity: City approaching modern. Established, confident, clearly
recovered.
Run environment: Full mechanical complexity unlocked. All systems active.
Higher difficulty.
Difficulty: Late mid-game.
Training Center form: The Facility. Multi-story. Serious infrastructure.
More sections active, more of the player's power history visible.

STAGE FOUR — MODERN
Visual identity: Gleaming. SHIELD headquarters register. The hero is a
civic institution.
Run environment: Endless live game tail. Rex Flynn modifiers create
run-specific public challenges. Procedurally generated missions and bosses.
Maximum difficulty and replayability.
Difficulty: Maximum.
Training Center form: The Tower. Avengers Tower scale. Every proven power
section active and visible. Rex Flynn has a series about the building.
Citizens take photos outside it.

