6. EXPLORABLE CITY BUILDINGS — HADES HEADQUARTERS MODEL

The explorable buildings in Apex Chronicles follow the Hades headquarters
model:

- Buildings are spaces that grow and reflect the player's run history
- Mechanical action does not happen inside the buildings — it happens in runs
- Buildings are atmosphere, narrative, and interface
- Walking through a building at Stage Four tells the story of everything the
  player has done across the full run record
- New content surfaces in buildings between runs — messages, challenges
  queued, sections activating — giving the player a reason to visit without
  requiring them to manage systems there

This model applies to the Training Center, the Hero's Lair, and any other
explorable city building. The run is always where the story happens. The
building is always where the story lives.

---

7. POST-TUTORIAL CITY BUILDINGS

CLASS-SPECIFIC NARRATIVE LOCATIONS (one per class):
Four buildings, one per class. These buildings exist in the city from early
progression but appear non-descript until the mentor relationship unlocks
through class progression and playtime. At unlock, the building reveals what
it actually is — hidden in plain sight.

These buildings provide narrative justification for advanced class power
unlocks. The mechanical unlock requirement remains run-count based (10 runs /
30 runs). The building is the story of why the unlock happens — not the gate
that controls it.

- Brawler location — reveals on Brawler mentor introduction
- Speedster location — reveals on Speedster mentor introduction
- Tactician location — reveals on Tactician mentor introduction
- Blaster location — reveals on Blaster mentor introduction

Individual mentor character names, personalities, and building identities are
flagged for future development.

---

8. THE HERO'S LAIR — HEADQUARTERS

The lair is earned through tutorial arc completion, not discovered as a
restorable building. It does not follow the restoration model.

The lair is the hero's space. It grows as the player plays. It houses:
- Combo discovery log — trophy case of discovered combinations, each logged
  with the exact power combination required to trigger it
- Achievement displays
- Unlocked name history — every name the world has offered, which ones were
  adopted
- Cosmetic loadout management
- Run statistics

The lair does not unlock combos. It records them. Combos are discovered
organically during runs — Vampire Survivors style. The lair is where those
discoveries live permanently.

The lair is explorable. Like the Training Center, it reads differently at
Stage Four than it did when first earned. The space accumulates the player's
story visibly.

MASTERY SCOPE BOUNDARIES:
- Training Center — hero power deepening and sponsor challenges
- Class Mentor Buildings — class primary power advancement
- Hero's Lair — combo discovery log. May house future combo advancement
  mechanics as that system develops.

These three buildings handle mastery between them. Their scopes do not
overlap.

---

9. CITY RESTORATION MODEL

Players do not build the city. They restore it. Every building has a person
inside it. Every restoration is a relationship.

The act of restoring a building: player initiates, a short build animation
plays, the building exists in its restored state. The ceremony is brief.
The weight is in what the building does afterward — not in the moment of
placing it.

Negative run outcomes affect the city atmospherically — citizen behavior,
visual tone, ambient mood. Nothing is permanently lost. No progress is set
back. No construction is reversed. The city always recovers.

---

10. CITY AND RUN LAYER RELATIONSHIP

The run layer and city layer share the same street map. The player is always
fighting in their city.

WHAT PROPAGATES FROM CITY TO RUN LAYER:
- Stage-level visual identity (Rundown, Developing, Refined, Modern)
- Core Four building landmarks visible in run environment
- Stage-level difficulty and enemy density

WHAT DOES NOT PROPAGATE FROM CITY TO RUN LAYER:
- Incremental cosmetic improvements within a stage
- Individual building restoration states
- Power pool gating of any kind

WHAT FLOWS FROM RUN TO CITY:
- Resources (from Boss Fight) — feeds city construction
- Morale (from Escort Defense) — primary driver of city atmospheric state
- Morale (from minor objectives) — secondary contribution; citizens in
  the area where the engagement happened noticed, and the neighborhood
  reflects it
- Intel (from Horde Survival) — identifies area villain, triggers area
  boss encounter

NOTE: XP and Hero Points from minor objectives feed intra-run progression
and the player's permanent currency — they are run-layer outputs, not
city-layer inputs. See Run Design document for full minor objectives
specification.

---

11. THE SUPERHERO COMMUNITY CHANNEL — CITY LAYER FUNCTION

The Superhero Community channel's primary reward pillar is player cosmetics.
Within the city layer, the channel additionally serves as the delivery
mechanism for the hero power deepening sponsorship system:

- Sponsor messages surface through this channel when a hero power is proven
- The channel tracks discipleship — whose disciples are proving themselves
- Sponsorship announcements are world events the channel broadcasts
- The community has opinions about mentors taking on unknown heroes

The channel is additionally a name emergence source. Names that
surface through the Superhero Community carry a peer/professional
register — how the hero world itself decides to categorize this
new arrival.

Cosmetics remain the primary reward pillar. Sponsorship and discipleship
tracking are the channel's mechanical function within the city layer. These
are parallel, not competing.

---

NON-NEGOTIABLE CONSTRAINTS:
- City buildings are mirrors, not gates. No exceptions.
- Discovery is always free. The full hero power pool is available from run
  one regardless of city state.
- Nothing is permanently lost. No construction is reversed. The city always
  recovers.
- Stage progression drives city development. Individual building restoration
  does not gate stage progression.
- The Training Center houses hero power deepening only — not class primary
  power improvement.
- The Hero's Lair records combos. It does not unlock them.
- The city is restored, not built. Every building has a person. Every
  restoration is a relationship.
- Explorable buildings follow the Hades headquarters model — atmosphere,
  narrative, and interface. Mechanical action happens in runs.
- Tone: comic book kinetic. The city should feel like a place worth
  protecting, not a management interface.

